The OPD is dropping off with higher Bi3+ concentration, while the Vo has a substantial growth, and Fig. 5 gives the graphical demonstration. The above two statements simultaneously are pointing out an increase in non-BO. The bond density (nb) of any matrix will be altered by incorporating a heavy-metal ion like Bi3+. And nb showing a negative trend with the Bi3+ concentration.15nb=NAVm∑ixnci=NAVmm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
